<div id="review_1200567076" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1200567076" />
    <a title="Skip" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1389748-skip"><img alt="Skip" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1231161516p2/1389748.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1200567076?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Skip" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Skip" href="/user/show/1389748-skip">Skip</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780375405389" href="/book/show/1786806.The_Power_of_the_Dog">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1389748-skip?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1200567076" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7769081539312820715">A dark novel by Californian Don Winslow about the never-ending &quot;war on drugs&quot; and the various efforts of the U.S. government and its agencies to support or destabilize political regimes in Latin America (a/k/a geopolitical meddling), from the mid-70s thru the late 1990s Most of the novel centers on a Mexican crime family, an honorable DEA agent who slowly loses his soul, and a few Mafioso from NY. Well-researched but also extremely violent with repeated, cataclysmic collateral damage. However, t</span>
  <span id="freeText7769081539312820715" style="display:none">A dark novel by Californian Don Winslow about the never-ending "war on drugs" and the various efforts of the U.S. government and its agencies to support or destabilize political regimes in Latin America (a/k/a geopolitical meddling), from the mid-70s thru the late 1990s Most of the novel centers on a Mexican crime family, an honorable DEA agent who slowly loses his soul, and a few Mafioso from NY. Well-researched but also extremely violent with repeated, cataclysmic collateral damage. However, the book wandered off point extensively in the first half, especially an unnecessary start with a scene from much later in the novel. The second half was better, but could have been better edited. Some good complex characters, each with his or her own flaws Father Prada, Nora, Tio, Adan, Art Keller, and Sean Callan.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7769081539312820715" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


