    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1664742086" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1664742086" />
    <a title="RJ - Slayer of Trolls" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/131730-rj---slayer-of-trolls"><img alt="RJ - Slayer of Trolls" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1644082981p2/131730.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1664742086?book_show_action=true">Jan 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="RJ - Slayer of Trolls" class="user" itemprop="url" name="RJ - Slayer of Trolls" href="/user/show/131730-rj---slayer-of-trolls">RJ - Slayer of Trolls</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1664742086" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1515064277655779574">If Winslow has a magnum opus, this is certainly it. A historical novel of the history of the Mexican drug cartels, with a stupefyingly-epic scope that reaches all the way back to the Vietnam War and continues through the late 1990s, encompassing real life political events such as the Phoenix Program and Operation Condor, all twisted together with the barely fictional characters until you won&apos;t be able to tell what&apos;s real and what isn&apos;t. Squeamish readers take note: there are massive amounts of p</span>
  <span id="freeText1515064277655779574" style="display:none">If Winslow has a magnum opus, this is certainly it. A historical novel of the history of the Mexican drug cartels, with a stupefyingly-epic scope that reaches all the way back to the Vietnam War and continues through the late 1990s, encompassing real life political events such as the Phoenix Program and Operation Condor, all twisted together with the barely fictional characters until you won't be able to tell what's real and what isn't. Squeamish readers take note: there are massive amounts of potentially objectionable material including sex, violence, profanity, drugs, and the Catholic Church. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1515064277655779574" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

