    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3992040240" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3992040240" />
    <a title="Ginger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14097149-ginger"><img alt="Ginger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1644286916p2/14097149.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3992040240?book_show_action=true">May 29, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ginger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ginger" href="/user/show/14097149-ginger">Ginger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781433245480" href="/book/show/10412721-the-power-of-the-dog">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Ginger by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/12949855-corey">Corey</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=library-book">library-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14097149-ginger?shelf=audio">audio</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3992040240" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5383643299365627230"><b>Wow! This is an unrelenting look into cartels, the drug trade, and the government organizations that try and put a bandaid on the problem!</b><br/><br/><b>The Power of the Dog</b> is the first book in the series, <u>Power of the Dog</u>.<br/><br/>I decided to do the audiobook for this book and series because <i>Ray Porter</i> is the godfather when it comes to doing narration.<br/>In fact, I don’t think there’s a book that he’s narrated that I didn’t love!<br/><br/><b>The Power of the Dog</b> follows the beginning of the Barrera brothers and family as they becom</span>
  <span id="freeText5383643299365627230" style="display:none"><b>Wow! This is an unrelenting look into cartels, the drug trade, and the government organizations that try and put a bandaid on the problem!</b><br /><br /><b>The Power of the Dog</b> is the first book in the series, <u>Power of the Dog</u>.<br /><br />I decided to do the audiobook for this book and series because <i>Ray Porter</i> is the godfather when it comes to doing narration.<br />In fact, I don’t think there’s a book that he’s narrated that I didn’t love!<br /><br /><b>The Power of the Dog</b> follows the beginning of the Barrera brothers and family as they become the kingpins to one of the most powerful and brutal cartels in Mexico.<br />And trying to stop the brutality of the cartel and flow of drugs into the states is a DEA agent named Art Keller.<br /><br />I loved Agent Art Keller and all the characters in this book. Nora Hayden, Sean Callan and Father Parada were my favorites. <u>And all for different reasons.</u><br /><br /><i>Don Winslow</i> does not let you feel mild or bland about any characters in this book.<br />There’s a love/hate feel to each one. Some of the decisions and actions they make in this book will leave you gutted and feel rage.<br /><br />In fact, this is an unflinching look into cartels and the actions they take against rivals, innocent citizens and anyone that gets in their way.<br />The deaths are traumatic, the sex is raw, and the violence will make you feel sad and frustrated. <br /><br />Honestly, I didn’t feel like it was too much.<br /><br />Is the writer <i>Don Winslow</i> trying to shock the reader for unnecessary reasons? <b>No.</b><br />It felt appropriate, honest and exactly what happens in a book about the cartel and drug trade.<br /><br /><u>If you want real horror, look no further.</u><br /><br /><b>Definitely read this one if you like action, well-written characters and books that will grip the living hell out of you.</b><br /><br />I looking forward to getting to the next book in the series. In fact, I’m going to take a few months to get to the second book, <b>The Cartel</b> because I think I need a bit of a breather.<br /><br />Now where’s my horror and thriller books that don’t feel so real?! ha!! 🤣😂</span>
  <a data-text-id="5383643299365627230" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


