        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2620870707" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2886477057454041123">As much a textbook on the political and economics of the war on drugs as it is a thriller, Winslow&apos;s book is as entertaining as it is disturbing. Sadly, there is far too much nonfiction in the pages, nonfiction that shed a glowing light on American foreign policy.<br/><br/>My thanks to the folks at the <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/19126-the-mystery-crime-and-thriller-group' rel='nofollow noopener'> The Mystery, Crime, and Thriller Group</a> for giving me the opportunity to read and discuss this and many other fine books.</span>
  <span id="freeText2886477057454041123" style="display:none">As much a textbook on the political and economics of the war on drugs as it is a thriller, Winslow's book is as entertaining as it is disturbing. Sadly, there is far too much nonfiction in the pages, nonfiction that shed a glowing light on American foreign policy.<br /><br />My thanks to the folks at the <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/19126-the-mystery-crime-and-thriller-group" rel="nofollow noopener"> The Mystery, Crime, and Thriller Group</a> for giving me the opportunity to read and discuss this and many other fine books.</span>
