<div id="review_3325448880" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3325448880" />
    <a title="Tony" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5456932-tony"><img alt="Tony" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552330577p2/5456932.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3325448880?book_show_action=true">Jun 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tony" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tony" href="/user/show/5456932-tony">Tony</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11227317-the-power-of-the-dog">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5456932-tony?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3325448880" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3325989135151719239">I know it’s a cliche but this really is a rollercoaster of a book. It’s absolutely relentless, epic in its scope and cinematic in its delivery. It’s also cleverly written with lots of different and distinct “voices” - the dogged DEA agent, merciless drug-lords, mobsters, hitmen... The only thing that stops it being a five-star book, in my view, is that its relentless pace leaves insufficient time for character development. But it’s a fair trade-off. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


